@comment{===================================================================}
@comment{
Domain Focus: This domain examines how AI systems affect public
knowledge, democratic discourse, and collective epistemic agency. Key
themes include: AI's impact on democratic citizenship and political
agency, population-level belief polarization or convergence through AI,
epistemic foundations of democracy, collective epistemic agency in
AI-mediated environments, and AI governance from epistemic perspective.

Search Strategy: PhilPapers (AI + democracy, AI + public knowledge),
Journal of Political Philosophy, Political Theory, Philosophy & Public
Affairs, AI and Ethics, Science and Engineering Ethics, SSRN

Key Questions:
- How do AI systems affect public knowledge and democratic discourse?
- Does AI cause population-level belief polarization or convergence?
- What are epistemic aspects of AI governance?
- How is collective epistemic agency affected by AI-mediated
  environments?
- What epistemic foundations does democracy require?
}
